Package net.xqhs.flash.core.agent

Class AgentWave

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.xqhs.util.config.Config
      • net.xqhs.flash.core.util.MultiValueMap
        • net.xqhs.flash.core.agent.AgentEvent
          • net.xqhs.flash.core.agent.AgentWave
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.xqhs.util.config.Configurable
    public class AgentWave
extends AgentEvent
    The wave is a type of event that conveys information between two entities, whether these entities are agents, shards inside different agents, or shards inside the same agent.

    A wave has a source and one or more possible destinations, all of which are endpoints, as well as a content and any number of other properties. Since AgentWave extends MultiValueMap, all properties are accessible via their keys. In order to facilitate routing waves, we define the following elements of a wave (for which there are methods defined):

    • the content - property CONTENT. The main content of the wave.
    • path elements of the source endpoint - values of the property SOURCE_ELEMENT.
    • the complete source, representing the complete source endpoint as generated from the path elements.
    • the destinations, as complete endpoints - values of the property COMPLETE_DESTINATION.
      • The intention is that these values should remain unchanged throughout the lifetime of the wave.
      • There may be multiple destinations for a wave.
    • path elements of a destination - values of the property DESTINATION_ELEMENT.
      • It may be useful that routers of the wave change this property in order to remove the elements that have already been considered in the routing, leaving the next element to be processed by the next router.
      • It is also up to routers to manage the elements in the case of multiple destinations, as the DESTINATION_ELEMENT name can only be associated with the elements of a single "complete" destination.

      • AgentWave

        public AgentWave​(java.lang.String content,
                 java.lang.String destinationRoot,
                 java.lang.String... destinationElements)
        Creates an agent wave with a single destination.

        A complete destination will be added by assembling the elements of the destination.

        The content argument may be a serialized form produced by getSerializedContent() and, if so, the content will be unpacked accordingly.

        Parameters:
        content - - the content of the wave, that can be the result of previous serialization.
        destinationRoot - - the first element of the destination endpoint.
        destinationElements - - other elements of the destination endpoint.

      • makePath

        public static java.lang.String makePath​(java.lang.String start,
                                        java.lang.String... elements)
        Produces an endpoint description by assembling the start of the address with the rest of the elements. They will be separated by what is the value of the ADDRESS_SEPARATOR.

        Elements that are null will not be assembled in the path.

        If the start is null the result will begin with a slash.

        Parameters:
        start - - start of the address. Special cases:
        • null - the path will start with the first element.
        • ADDRESS_SEPARATOR - the path will start with "/", followed by the first element
        elements - - other elements in the address
        Returns:
        the resulting address.

      • pathToElements

        public static java.lang.String[] pathToElements​(java.lang.String path,
                                                java.lang.String prefixToRemove)
        Splits a complete endpoint (a path) into its elements. This version also removes the specified prefix from the path, so it will not be included in the returned elements.

        The path is split by ADDRESS_SEPARATOR.

        If the path does not begin with the given prefix, the prefix will be ignored.

        Parameters:
        path - - the endpoint description to split.
        prefixToRemove - - the prefix to remove from the endpoint.
        Returns:
        the elements of the path, excluding the prefix.

      • pathToElementsWith

        public static java.lang.String[] pathToElementsWith​(java.lang.String path,
                                                    java.lang.String prefix)
        Splits a complete endpoint (a path) into its elements. This version allows the caller to specify a prefix, which will be returned as the first element of the path.

        The path is split by ADDRESS_SEPARATOR.

        If the path does not begin with the given prefix, the prefix will be ignored.

        Parameters:
        path - - the endpoint description to split.
        prefix - - the prefix of the endpoint to consider as the first element.
        Returns:
        the elements of the path, including the prefix.
